  "prompt": "What were Edwin Hubble works? How did he achieve them?",
  "response": "Edwin Hubble was an influential astronomer whose work dramatically changed our understanding of the universe. Below are some of his most notable contributions and the methods he used to achieve them:\n\n1. **Detection of galaxies beyond the Milky Way:**\n   - **Contribution:** Hubble demonstrated that many objects previously thought to be nebulae within the Milky Way were actually separate galaxies located outside of it. This was a fundamental shift from the \"island universe\" hypothesis to the recognition of a much larger and diverse universe.\n   - **Method:** He used the Hooker Telescope at the Mount Wilson Observatory, which was then the largest optical telescope in the world. By observing Cepheid variable stars in the Andromeda galaxy and calculating their distances using the period-luminosity relationship, Hubble was able to show that these stars were far too distant to be part of the Milky Way.\n\n2. **Expansion of the Universe:**\n   - **Contribution:** Hubble discovered that galaxies are moving away from us and that their velocity increases with distance from Earth, leading to the formulation of Hubble's Law, which implies the universe is expanding. This observation provided foundational support for the Big Bang theory.\n   - **Method:** Using redshift data from the spectra of various galaxies, Hubble observed that the light from these galaxies was shifted towards the red end of the spectrum, indicating they were receding. By plotting this redshift against the distance of the galaxies (calculated through various methods), he found a linear relationship, now known as the Hubble constant.\n\n3. **Hubble Sequence:**\n   - **Contribution:** Hubble developed a classification system for galaxies, known as the Hubble Sequence or Hubble Tuning Fork Diagram. This system categorizes galaxies based on their morphology as elliptical, spiral, or lenticular types and helps in understanding galaxy formation and evolution.\n   - **Method:** Through meticulous observation and detailed photography, primarily using the Hooker Telescope, Hubble categorized and analyzed the shapes and sizes of numerous galaxies, establishing a systematic approach to galaxy classification.\n\nThese accomplishments were made possible through Hubble's pioneering use of advanced telescopic technology, his meticulous observational techniques, and his capacity for groundbreaking scientific insight. His work laid the foundation for much of modern cosmology and continues to influence our understanding of the universe.",
